description:
This is a free/open available merged checkpoint model.

If you like my work, feel free to buy me a coffee at ko-fi. https://ko-fi.com/mixboy

WARNING: Anything v3.x model is a trained model based on the original Novel AI Leakage and which might cause a License issue. (https://www.bilibili.com/read/cv19603218 )

All models have merged with the SuperMerger extension

  • chillyMixBaseV0 described in the chillySauceMix by @mixboy

  • anything v3.2 at Hugging Face

so this model includes well-known legacy checkpoints as follows:

  • pyro's_pov models - (pyro_pov_a + pyro_pov_b)

  • F222 (Fp32) see also F222 at https://rentry.co/sdmodels

  • r34_e4 (Fp16) - from https://rentry.co/sdmodels

  • and anything v3.2 at Hugging Face

Merge Recipe

by SuperMerger extension following two-step merge can be done in one step:

  • (chillyMixBaseV0 x 0.8 +anything-v3-2-Fp16Fixed x 0.2) x 0.4 + neverendingDreamNED_noVae-Fix x 0.6

the ChillyMixBaseV0 model alone is not good enough to use alone. It produces overfitted results sometimes. adding anything-v3 reduces this issue significantly and add NED(NeverEndingDream - NO VAE version) again to make it more robust and good enough for normal use.

  • overall anything-v3-2 contribution = 0.2 x 0.4 = 0.08 (anime style)

  • overall r34 contribution = 0.25 x 0.4 x 0.8 = 0.08 (anime style)

What's the difference

and what are the advantages of this unlike anything other models?

  • first, its recipe is open, anyone who wants to change the results a bit can change their recipe based on it.

  • more realistic body/skin

  • less realistic face (2.5D style): r32_e4 + anything-v3.2 contribute to it.

  • less Asian style - you can use the PureErosFace(v1) embedding for Asian women.

What's the difference between chillySauceMix

  • sweetChillyMix includes the Anything-v3.2 :)

  • famous well-known legacy checkpoints are included.

  • basically, chillySauceMix is for checkpoint developer/merger but SweetChillyMix is for normal usage.

Recommends

  • default Clip skip is 2, ETA noise seed delta: 31337

  • chilloutmix based LoRA works fine.

Useful AUTOMATIC1111's webui extensions

  • SuperMerger extension

  • Lora Block Weight extension

  • webui model toolkit to examine Loras and models.

  • civitai extension to add several useful features for civitai.

  • ADetailer or DDetailer to enhance face details.
